cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the efficiency of statistical parsers, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a machine-independent metric for measuring efficiency, which involves probability calculations, suggesting that it could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper may be of interest to researchers working on information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS) due to its focus on measuring efficiency.
